race.comment: HURRICANE THUNDER (5) is racing very well, placing two back before a big win last time over 1300m at Longreach. Expected to measure up again. CENTRE BOUNCE (1) hasn't raced since being well held in richer grade at Doomben earlier this year. Resumes from a long spell for a new stable and is well placed in this company. Watch the betting very closely. NAPOLEON STRIKE (3) was well bet but ran below expectations when sixth over 1360m at Gordonvale. Form at this distance is strong with five wins from nine starts and is a key contender. PENNYPACKER (4) was safely held last time but a winner the start prior and gets a chance to bounce back.
